# Default unit policy for Flatpak setup.
#
# flathub-remote-add.service is a oneshot that configures the Flathub
# remote (--if-not-exists, system-wide) at first network availability.
# Vendor-neutral: downstream distros that prefer a different remote
# (e.g. razorfin's own mirror, or Fedora's flatpak remote) can drop a
# 92-<thing>.preset that disables this and enables their alternative.

enable flathub-remote-add.service
